{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":790,"text":"The filmmaker Georges Méliès was first a magician."},{"time":6881,"text":"Now movies proved to be the ultimate medium for magic."},{"time":13641,"text":"With complete control of everything the audience can see,"},{"time":19122,"text":"moviemakers had developed an arsenal of techniques"},{"time":23479,"text":"to further their deceptions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27773,"text":"Motion pictures are themselves an illusion of life,"},{"time":32588,"text":"produced by the sequential projection of still frames,"},{"time":36431,"text":"and they astonished the Lumière brothers' early audiences."},{"time":41299,"text":"Even today's sophisticated moviegoers"},{"time":43995,"text":"still lose themselves to the screen,"},{"time":46915,"text":"and filmmakers leverage this separation from reality"},{"time":50595,"text":"to great effect."},{"time":53142,"text":"Now imaginative people have been having fun with this"},{"time":57452,"text":"for over 400 years."},{"time":59521,"text":"Giambattista della Porta, a Neapolitan scholar"},{"time":63322,"text":"in the 16th century, examined and studied the natural world"},{"time":68924,"text":"and saw how it could be manipulated."},{"time":72571,"text":"Playing with the world, and our perception of it,"},{"time":75987,"text":"really is the essence of visual effects."},{"time":79277,"text":"So digging deeper into this"},{"time":81459,"text":"with the Science and Technology Council"},{"time":83811,"text":"of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences"},{"time":86971,"text":"reveals some truth behind the trickery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91459,"text":"Visual effects are based on the principles of all illusions:"},{"time":96803,"text":"assumption, things are as we know them;"},{"time":100483,"text":"presumption, things will behave as we expect;"},{"time":104556,"text":"and context in reality,"},{"time":107053,"text":"our knowledge of the world as we know it,"},{"time":109645,"text":"such as scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111247,"text":"Now a fourth factor really becomes an obsession,"},{"time":115324,"text":"which is, never betray the illusion."},{"time":119429,"text":"And that last point has made visual effects"},{"time":122532,"text":"a constant quest for perfection."},{"time":125884,"text":"So from the hand-cranked jump cut early days of cinema"},{"time":130611,"text":"to last Sunday's Oscar winner, what follows are some steps"},{"time":135691,"text":"and a few repeats in the evolution of visual effects."},{"time":140898,"text":"I hope you will enjoy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144386,"text":"Isabelle: \"The filmmaker Georges Méliès"},{"time":149349,"text":"was one of the first to realize that"},{"time":153725,"text":"films had the power"},{"time":156357,"text":"to capture dreams.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":158933,"text":"(Music) [\"'A Trip to the Moon' (1902)\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162206,"text":"[\"2011 Restoration of the Original Hand-Tinted Color\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175045,"text":"[\"'2001: A Space Odyssey' (1968)\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178891,"text":"[\"Academy Award Winner for Visual Effects\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189746,"text":"[\"'Avatar' (2009)\"] First doctor: How are you feeling, Jake?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191866,"text":"Jake: Hey guys."},{"time":193320,"text":"[\"Academy Award Winner for Visual Effects\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194322,"text":"Second doctor: Welcome to your new body, Jake.First doctor: Good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197710,"text":"Second doctor: We're gonna take this nice and easy, Jake.First doctor: Well, do you want to sit up? That's fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201029,"text":"Second doctor: And good, just take it nice and slow, Jake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202941,"text":"Well, no truncal ataxia, that's good.First doctor: You feeling light-headed or dizzy at all?"},{"time":206597,"text":"Oh, you're wiggling your toes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208392,"text":"[\"'Alice's Adventures in Wonderland' (1972)\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210801,"text":"Alice: What's 